==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*fēra-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[var|vār]] ‘ambush’ (Dutch [[gevaar]] ‘danger’), Old High German [[fara|fāra]] ‘ambush, danger, deceit’ (German [[Gefahr]] ‘danger’).

====Pronunciation====
[[IPA]]: /fæ:r/

====Noun====
'''fǣr''' ''m''
# a sudden [[danger]] or [[calamity]]; an [[ambush]]

====Descendents====
*English [[fear]]

===Etymology===
From the same Germanic source as [[faran]].  Cognate with Old High German [[fuora]] (German [[Fuhre]]).

====Pronunciation====
[[IPA]]: /fær/

====Noun====
'''fær''' ''n''
# a [[journey]], a [[coming]] or [[going]]

====Descendents====
*English [[fare]]

